\n<Manu><WordWrap>CHEF, Good news!
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>What happened?
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Paz Latchoy has given me a second chance to compete in the competition. Now I can proceed to the next level.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>But there is some bad news...
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>What's the badnews?

\n<Manu><WordWrap>Well you see, it was a made up contest but Paz Latchoy still gave me a chance and allowed me to proceed. However,he said that I should meet the mayor so that I can be officially participate in the competition. He gave me a letter with all the details.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Do you know by chance where the mayor of Gastropolis would be?
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Hmmmm. Well I think I know where he might be at.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Exactly where?
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Its a stretch but he might be at the Town Hall.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>We'll head there right now.
<actionIcon: 468>
\n<Manu><WordWrap>There you are CHEF I have been looking for you every where!
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Sorry Manu, I was talking with Belle about what Paz Latchoy did.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>But nevermind that for now. What happened with you and the mayor?
\n<Manu><WordWrap>He gave me a chance to compete in the competition. Not only that but he allowed me to proceed to the new area called the Islands and Customes?
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Now I understand what he meant by that.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>The next area of the competition is a faw away iland that you will need to take by boat.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>You will need to reach the Customes of Gastropolis which is located in the Esplanade of the city.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>It's at the far right of the city itself. follow the roads that lead to the right side of Gastropolis.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>I'll head out first to the Customes. You can venture around the city of Gastropolis first to get yourself familiarize with its surroundings.
